<P>A di&s;tant echo lengthened out her tones, and &s;he &s;at li&s;ten|ing to the &s;oft re&s;pon&s;e, till repeating the la&s;t &s;tanza of the Sonnet, &s;he was an&s;wered by a voice almo&s;t as tender, and le&s;s di&s;tant. She looked round in &s;urpri&s;e, and &s;aw a young man in a hunter's dre&s;s, leaning again&s;t a tree, and gazing on her with that deep attention, which marks an enraptured mind.</P>
<P>A thou&s;and apprehen&s;ions her athwart her bu&s;y thought&punc; and &s;he now fir&s;t remembered her di&s;tance from the abbey. She ro&s;e in ha&s;te to be gone, when the &s;tranger re&s;pectfuly advanc|ed; but, ob&s;erving her timid looks and retiring &s;teps, he pau&s;ed She pur&s;ued her way towards the abbey&punc; and though many rea&s;on made her anxious to know whether &s;he was followed, delicacy forbade her to look back. When &s;he reached the abbey finding the family was not yet a&s;&s;embled to breakfa&s;t, &s;he re|tired to her chamber, where her whole thoughts were employe<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> in conjectures concerning the &s;tranger&punc; believing that &s;he <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> intere&s;ted on this point no farther than a<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> it concerned the &s;a<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> of La Motte, &s;he indulged without &s;cruple, the remembra<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ce <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> that dignified air and manner which &s;o much di&s;tingui&s;hed <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> youth &s;he had &s;een. After <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">olving the circum&s;tance m<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> deeply, &s;he believed it impo&s;&s;ible that a per&s;on of his appearan<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> &s;hould be engaged in a &s;tratag<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">m to betray a fellow crea<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> and though &s;he was de&s;tit<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">te of a &s;ingle circum&s;tance that m<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> a&s;&s;i&s;t her &s;urmi&s;es of who he was, or what was his bu&s;ine&s;s i<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> unfreque<GAP DESC="illegib