<P><PB N="83" REF="029379_0042_0FE08A84A7DF5DF0">"My chief re&s;idence," &s;aid the Marquis, "is in a di&s;tant province, but I have a chateau near the borders of the fore&s;t, and in returning from an excur&s;ion, I have been benighted and lo&s;t my way. A light which gleamed through the trees, attract|ed me hither, and, &s;uch was the darkne&s;s without, that I did not know it proceeded from the abbey till I came to the door." The noble deportment of the &s;trangers, the &s;plendour of their apparel, and above all, this &s;peech di&s;&s;ipated every remaining doubt of Madame's, and &s;he was giving orders for refre&s;hments to be &s;et before them, when La Motte, who had li&s;tened, and was now convinced he had nothing to fear, entered the apartment.</P>
