<P>The Marquis, &s;eeming to recover his pre&s;ence of mind, &s;tepped to the door of the hall where his people were a&s;&s;embled, when La Motte, &s;tarting from his &s;eat, with a frantic air, called on him to return. The Marquis looked back and &s;topped, but &s;till he&s;itating whether to proceed; the &s;upplica|tions of Adeline, who was now returned, added to tho&s;e of La Motte, determined him, and he &s;at down. "I reque&s;t of you, my Lord," &s;aid La Motte, "that we may conver&s;e for a few moments by our&s;elves."</P>
