<P>Hither the Marquis and La Motte &s;oon followed, the <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> haughty and cool, the latter &s;omewhat more compo&s;ed th<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> before, though the impre&s;&s;ion of horror was not yet faded fro<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> his countenance. The Marquis pa&s;&s;ed on to the hall where <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> retinue awaited: the &s;torm was not yet &s;ub&s;ided, but he &s;e<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> impatient to be gone, and ordered his people to be in readin<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> La Motte ob&s;erved a &s;ullen &s;ilence, frequently pacing the <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word">
